Nutritional side of hemp

-Complete protein with all 9 amino acids
-Essential fatty acids, including omega 3s. Body can't produce these fats, must absorb from diet. Ideal Omega 3 to 6 ratio, helpful for animals that consume hemp seeds as feed (hens, cows, etc..)
-Good source of fiber
-Minerals and vitamins
    -vitamin E
    -magnesium
    -phosphorous
    -potassium
    -niacin
    -riboflavin
    -thiamine
    -B6
    -folate
-Neuroprotective, anti-inflammatory, helps regulate immune system
-

Uses

-Hemp seeds in raw from
-Seed flour
-Tea    
-Milk
